cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper deals with learning cross-modal representations using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new cross-modal scene dataset, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these representations for retrieval, which could also fall under natural language processing (cs.CL).
